'''Afro-Anguillians''' or '''Black Anguillians''' are [[Demographics of Anguilla|Anguillian]] whose ancestry lies within the continent of [[Africa]], most notably [[West Africa]].
As of 2013, people of solely African descent are the majority ethnic group in [[Anguilla]], accounting for 90.1% of the country's population. An additional 4.6% of the country is [[mulatto]].<ref name=cia>{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/av.html |title=CIA - The World Factbook -- Cayman Islands |accessdate=2013-06-09 |publisher=CIA | archiveurl= https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/av.html| archivedate= 14 May 2013 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref>
