The '''Sikiana''' are an [[indigenous people of the Americas|indigenous people]], living in [[Brazil]], [[Suriname]], and [[Venezuela]].<ref name=ethno/>

==Name==
The Sikiana are also called Chikena, Chiquena, Chiquiana, Shikiana, Sikiâna, Sikiyana, Sikiána, Sikïiyana, Tshikiana, Xikiyana, or Xikujana people.<ref name=ethno/>

==Language==
The [[Sikiana language]] belongs to the [[Carib language]] family. Some Sikiana people in Venezuela speak the [[Trío language]].<ref name=ethno/>

